===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[aero-]]'', combining form for '''air''' + plane, from Latin ''[[planum]]'', '''flat'''

# A powered [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]].

